{"word":"νομεύς","slug":"νομεύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νομεύς</b></el> <el>(νομεύς, έως,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νέμω'><el>νέμω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a shepherd, herdsman</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a dealer out, distributer</i>, <el>ἀγαθῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>νομέες</el>, <i>the ribs of a ship</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}